Q: I need help! The girl who sits in the cubicle across from me is absolutely awful to me. She makes me dread work and I am on the verge of quitting. WHAT DO I DO?

A: This is truly unfortunate! You spend a big chunk of your life at work - so when a coworker makes you miserable, that can make life tricky. However, before you start applying to new jobs, let's try to identify the REAL problem. Do you two have a relationship conflict or performance conflict? Once you answer that, then we can really get to the bottom of how to resolve it. Check out this article on how to identify to "kind" of conflict you have--> https://randstad.us/2pnaQqf If you check out the tips in the article, and a resolve still cannot be made, then perhaps a new job might be best. (In which case, we'd love to guide you on that as well!)

post_text:
Q: Why would people waste their time with a recruiter when we can search on job boards for free?

A: If you can navigate your entire career completely on your own, using only job boards, we applaud you! A career is a journey, not a destination. Some companies are tough to get into unless "you know someone who knows someone."

We want to be THAT SOMEONE for you :) Also - a lot of people come to us because they want to change job industries. Going from a warehouse to a corporate office (or vice versa) can be stressful without the proper help and guidance. Recruiters partner with you and assist with that transition. See our blog post for more info about this: https://randstad.us/2Kwg2jA

If you want to #AskUs and our dedicated recruiters a question about #jobseeking or for career advice, let us know!

post_text:
Comment: I read your advice to the young buck asking about warehouse jobs and I appreciated all that was said. I have been a forklift operator for 23 years and I love my job. No suit and tie for me EVER! Although my wife probably wishes I did something other than sit and drive all day! That's the one draw back - I certainly pack on the pounds! HA!

Response: Thanks for reading our advice posts! I know our clients' companies couldn't thrive without all the dedicated workers in their warehouses! As for the weight-gain issue - have you read our insight about staying fit? Check this out -https://randstad.us/2M3ces4

If you want to leave us a comment, or #AskUs a question about #jobseeking or career advice, let us know!
